1
00:00:00,253 --> 00:00:01,486
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,486 --> 00:00:02,686
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:08,506 --> 00:00:11,606
(Violation Concerning Major Accidents,
Defendant, Seo Gwon Sik)

4
00:00:12,346 --> 00:00:15,892
"The defendant is hereby sentenced
to five years in prison?"

5
00:00:15,893 --> 00:00:17,226
(The defendant is hereby sentenced
to five years in prison.)

6
00:00:19,886 --> 00:00:20,886
That's impossible.

7
00:00:21,773 --> 00:00:24,586
Dad... He...

8
00:00:26,253 --> 00:00:28,686
Honey, why are you home so early?

9
00:00:29,506 --> 00:00:30,506
(Episode 68)

10
00:00:30,506 --> 00:00:32,799
The chairman wasn't feeling well
after the competition,

11
00:00:33,079 --> 00:00:34,933
so I took him home early
and came straight home.

12
00:00:35,146 --> 00:00:38,219
Perfect timing.
Seung Ri got off work early too.

13
00:00:38,373 --> 00:00:39,626
We can have dinner together.

14
00:00:39,733 --> 00:00:41,013
Seung Ri's already home?

15
00:00:41,133 --> 00:00:42,999
Yeah. Go change and come out.

16
00:00:43,166 --> 00:00:44,166
I'll have dinner ready in no time.

17
00:00:45,253 --> 00:00:46,253
Okay.

18
00:00:49,680 --> 00:00:51,113
Dad, you're home already?

19
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:53,646
Yes. What brings you into my study?

20
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:57,452
There was a book of yours
I wanted to read,

21
00:00:57,452 --> 00:01:00,412
but I couldn't find it. I'll leave.

22
00:01:10,433 --> 00:01:12,933
("The Paradox of Economics")

23
00:01:30,819 --> 00:01:33,999
No way. How could Dad...

24
00:01:41,026 --> 00:01:42,026
Did you find anything?

25
00:01:42,506 --> 00:01:45,506
Yes. Five priors for fraud, blackmail,
assault, and voice phishing.

26
00:01:45,753 --> 00:01:48,760
Just a month after getting out,
he's back to voice phishing.

27
00:01:49,693 --> 00:01:52,153
Really? Keep following him.

28
00:01:52,659 --> 00:01:54,979
Once you locate the operation,
contact me immediately.

29
00:01:58,826 --> 00:02:00,352
Why haven't you even
changed your clothes yet?

30
00:02:02,233 --> 00:02:03,686
I was just about to.

31
00:02:04,866 --> 00:02:05,866
Seung Ri,

32
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:09,466
about the night you stayed out...

33
00:02:10,193 --> 00:02:12,912
Were you with Min Ho by any chance?

34
00:02:13,846 --> 00:02:14,846
What?

35
00:02:16,119 --> 00:02:17,952
No, it's nothing.

36
00:02:18,793 --> 00:02:19,893
Hurry and come eat.

37
00:02:20,113 --> 00:02:21,746
Your dad got home early for once.

38
00:02:21,826 --> 00:02:23,232
I'm not hungry.

39
00:02:23,700 --> 00:02:26,999
I only got three hours of sleep preparing
for the competition, so I want to sleep.

40
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,186
You should at least have a few bites.

41
00:02:29,413 --> 00:02:31,253
You shouldn't go to bed
on an empty stomach.

42
00:02:31,620 --> 00:02:33,866
I'll rest first and eat later.

43
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:35,000
All right, then.

44
00:02:37,826 --> 00:02:38,826
Listen...

45
00:02:39,386 --> 00:02:42,512
Since you've gone this far,
make up your mind, okay?

46
00:02:43,706 --> 00:02:44,706
What are you talking about?

47
00:02:46,033 --> 00:02:48,686
You and Min Ho...

48
00:02:50,093 --> 00:02:53,286
Please leave, Mom. I want to sleep.

49
00:02:53,746 --> 00:02:55,332
Okay. Get some rest.

50
00:03:03,533 --> 00:03:06,946
Mr. Seo told me
you weren't feeling well today.

51
00:03:07,979 --> 00:03:08,979
It's nothing.

52
00:03:10,033 --> 00:03:12,366
I was told I had six months
to a year left to live.

53
00:03:12,820 --> 00:03:15,120
But look at me now.
I'm still going strong.

54
00:03:16,933 --> 00:03:20,340
More importantly,
are you upset about what happened...

55
00:03:21,040 --> 00:03:22,040
right before the presentation?

56
00:03:22,666 --> 00:03:26,133
It caught me off guard, but fortunately,
it all worked out, so I'm fine.

57
00:03:26,606 --> 00:03:27,913
Please don't worry about me.

58
00:03:28,566 --> 00:03:30,319
How can I not?

59
00:03:31,493 --> 00:03:34,959
As soon as we find out
what really happened,

60
00:03:35,606 --> 00:03:37,506
I'm going to take follow-up action.

61
00:03:38,586 --> 00:03:39,586
Grandpa.

62
00:03:39,999 --> 00:03:42,633
Wouldn't it be better
to let this go quietly this time?

63
00:03:43,493 --> 00:03:45,405
If controversy erupts
during the competition,

64
00:03:45,406 --> 00:03:48,179
it won't do
the retirement community project any good.

65
00:03:49,439 --> 00:03:51,693
You think that was the first time
I've seen you like that?

66
00:03:52,646 --> 00:03:55,959
I remember it vividly
from your first day of elementary school.

67
00:03:57,273 --> 00:03:59,073
Min Ho, being a child,

68
00:03:59,346 --> 00:04:02,286
locked you in the attic
because he hated you.

69
00:04:02,586 --> 00:04:03,886
You were exactly the same that day.

70
00:04:05,579 --> 00:04:07,152
In that tiny attic,

71
00:04:07,606 --> 00:04:10,572
you couldn't even speak
and just trembled uncontrollably.

72
00:04:13,799 --> 00:04:17,439
As you grew older, the symptoms
seemed to disappear, so I was relieved.

73
00:04:18,339 --> 00:04:20,186
Is it still bothering you?

74
00:04:20,846 --> 00:04:23,979
I've just had a lot on my mind lately
and haven't been sleeping well.

75
00:04:24,266 --> 00:04:26,926
I'll be fine soon, so please don't worry.

76
00:04:27,853 --> 00:04:32,093
A wound doesn't disappear
just because you hide it.

77
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:36,853
If something's hurting,
you have to expose it and cut it out.

78
00:04:37,746 --> 00:04:39,119
If you don't pull it out by the roots,

79
00:04:40,006 --> 00:04:42,846
it'll fester again someday.

80
00:04:45,353 --> 00:04:48,173
Did today's presentation go well?

81
00:04:48,453 --> 00:04:49,453
Yes, Grandma.

82
00:04:49,659 --> 00:04:52,766
Ms. Cho Eun Ae gave Joy's presentation,
and she did an excellent job.

83
00:04:52,886 --> 00:04:53,886
Eun Ae did?

84
00:04:54,666 --> 00:04:57,419
Really? I'm sure she did great.

85
00:04:58,146 --> 00:04:59,319
You're staying the night, right?

86
00:04:59,706 --> 00:05:02,405
No. I'm just going to pack a few things
and head back.

87
00:05:02,406 --> 00:05:03,693
You rascal.

88
00:05:04,033 --> 00:05:06,746
Does that place already feel
more like home than this one?

89
00:05:07,966 --> 00:05:10,466
At least have dinner before you go,
all right?

90
00:05:11,006 --> 00:05:12,006
Yes, Grandma.

91
00:05:14,253 --> 00:05:15,253
Honey.

92
00:05:16,513 --> 00:05:19,146
How was it? Did Min Ho do well?

93
00:05:19,533 --> 00:05:20,866
I'm sure he did.

94
00:05:22,026 --> 00:05:23,465
- Where's Father?
- Well...

95
00:05:23,466 --> 00:05:26,379
He wasn't feeling well,
so Mr. Seo brought him home early.

96
00:05:26,673 --> 00:05:28,900
He's talking with Gyeol right now.

97
00:05:29,953 --> 00:05:31,613
Gyeol's here?

98
00:05:33,506 --> 00:05:35,546
- All right.
- That's right.

99
00:05:36,266 --> 00:05:37,719
Eun Ae confidently did such a great...

100
00:05:39,506 --> 00:05:42,606
Anyone would think Min Ho was a child
we picked off the street.

101
00:05:51,693 --> 00:05:52,793
Hey.

102
00:05:54,213 --> 00:05:55,986
What did Grandpa talk to you about?

103
00:05:56,766 --> 00:05:59,946
Did they find out
who was behind the video incident?

104
00:06:01,272 --> 00:06:02,459
No, we didn't talk about that.

105
00:06:03,853 --> 00:06:05,006
I see.

106
00:06:06,966 --> 00:06:08,133
You made quite an impression today,

107
00:06:09,059 --> 00:06:10,659
announcing your relationship
at the competition.

108
00:06:12,059 --> 00:06:15,766
What? Who announced their relationship?

109
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:17,959
Don't tell me Gyeol did.

110
00:06:18,133 --> 00:06:21,266
It wasn't how I wanted it to happen,
but it didn't turn out badly.

111
00:06:21,726 --> 00:06:23,986
At least we don't have to
keep hiding our relationship anymore.

112
00:06:27,253 --> 00:06:29,406
If that's all, I'll head upstairs.

113
00:06:29,606 --> 00:06:30,713
I need to pack a few things.

114
00:06:31,293 --> 00:06:32,293
Gyeol.

115
00:06:33,599 --> 00:06:34,893
Are you struggling that much?

116
00:06:35,853 --> 00:06:37,353
Should I introduce you to a psychiatrist?

117
00:06:38,467 --> 00:06:39,873
No, I'm fine.

118
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:41,739
Thank you for your concern.

119
00:06:48,626 --> 00:06:49,626
What are you talking about?

120
00:06:49,940 --> 00:06:52,486
What's wrong with Gyeol? A psychiatrist?

121
00:06:56,379 --> 00:06:58,533
Honey, what was that about?

122
00:08:13,393 --> 00:08:15,419
- I'm home.
- I'm home.

123
00:08:15,919 --> 00:08:18,505
- Grandpa.
- Hey, Bit Na.

124
00:08:18,505 --> 00:08:19,865
- You're back?
- Yeah.

125
00:08:20,326 --> 00:08:21,326
Let's go inside.

126
00:08:23,319 --> 00:08:25,019
We're home, honey.

127
00:08:25,020 --> 00:08:26,279
How come everyone's home all at once?

128
00:08:27,346 --> 00:08:28,653
What's all this?

129
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:30,999
Braised short ribs, marinated abalone...

130
00:08:31,226 --> 00:08:34,346
You only have to serve the soup and rice.
Have a good meal.

131
00:08:35,059 --> 00:08:36,659
Why? You should eat with us.

132
00:08:36,766 --> 00:08:39,666
I'm not hungry. Go ahead and eat.

133
00:08:41,586 --> 00:08:42,586
What's wrong with her?

134
00:08:44,566 --> 00:08:46,832
I think our grandmother made all this.

135
00:08:47,892 --> 00:08:50,506
You're right.
That's probably why she can't eat it.

136
00:08:51,140 --> 00:08:52,140
What should we do?

137
00:08:53,893 --> 00:08:56,133
Wait here. I'll go talk to her.

138
00:08:58,679 --> 00:08:59,679
Sit down.

139
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,506
So our grandmother came today.

140
00:09:05,106 --> 00:09:07,426
That's why she couldn't make it
to Bit Na's Mom Participation Day class.

141
00:09:09,186 --> 00:09:11,486
Dad, do you have a grandma too?

142
00:09:11,779 --> 00:09:13,225
I've never seen her.

143
00:09:13,226 --> 00:09:15,366
Actually, I've never met her either.

144
00:09:16,133 --> 00:09:17,506
- Auntie hasn't either.
- Why not?

145
00:09:18,232 --> 00:09:20,613
Cho Bit Na, what's that around your neck?

146
00:09:21,533 --> 00:09:24,039
Mom gave me a cell phone.

147
00:09:24,806 --> 00:09:25,939
Ji Seon came by today?

148
00:09:26,526 --> 00:09:28,073
She stopped by briefly to see Bit Na.

149
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:31,393
Mom promised she'd come to see me often.

150
00:09:32,546 --> 00:09:35,013
Really? That must make you happy, Bit Na.

151
00:09:36,900 --> 00:09:38,466
Come on. Let's eat together.

152
00:09:38,659 --> 00:09:41,786
If you keep this up, the kids
won't be able to eat comfortably either.

153
00:09:42,026 --> 00:09:44,426
Just eat. I told her to take it back,

154
00:09:44,853 --> 00:09:47,859
but she wanted you
and the kids to have it.

155
00:09:49,053 --> 00:09:50,526
How could she say something so shameless?

156
00:09:50,760 --> 00:09:52,926
She's just a mother
who wants to do something for her child.

157
00:09:53,939 --> 00:09:55,413
Couldn't you try to understand that?

158
00:09:55,586 --> 00:09:56,586
A mother?

159
00:09:57,386 --> 00:09:59,452
How can you say that so easily?

160
00:10:07,780 --> 00:10:08,780
What's this?

161
00:10:09,379 --> 00:10:12,006
A picture of you
based on your photo from the locket...

162
00:10:12,633 --> 00:10:14,113
and a current image of your mother.

163
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:18,326
Your mother and the Chairman...

164
00:10:18,786 --> 00:10:21,406
spent the last 50 years
desperately searching for you.

165
00:10:22,286 --> 00:10:25,599
There were mountains of documents
related to it.

166
00:10:26,586 --> 00:10:30,005
So what?

167
00:10:30,006 --> 00:10:31,553
Just because they spent all that time
searching for me,

168
00:10:32,180 --> 00:10:34,613
I'm supposed to erase the last 50 years?

169
00:10:37,286 --> 00:10:39,126
You're right. That isn't easy.

170
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,633
Fine. I'll just eat with the kids.

171
00:10:53,806 --> 00:10:55,119
How is this supposed to be me?

172
00:10:56,900 --> 00:10:58,000
It doesn't look like me at all.

173
00:11:06,773 --> 00:11:07,913
Why are you out here?

174
00:11:08,079 --> 00:11:09,153
Hey.

175
00:11:12,073 --> 00:11:13,073
Were you waiting for me?

176
00:11:13,833 --> 00:11:15,173
As if.

177
00:11:16,393 --> 00:11:17,706
It's nice.

178
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:20,433
Knowing someone
is actually waiting for me...

179
00:11:20,986 --> 00:11:22,625
How should I put it? My heart...

180
00:11:22,626 --> 00:11:24,859
feels all warm and tingly.

181
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:26,333
What?

182
00:11:27,253 --> 00:11:28,845
I heard you said that.

183
00:11:28,846 --> 00:11:31,746
That your heart felt all warm and tingly
whenever you thought of me.

184
00:11:32,459 --> 00:11:35,799
Come on!
Grandma Sun Bun misunderstood that part.

185
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:38,406
By the way, what's with the bag?

186
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:40,613
I brought some summer clothes...

187
00:11:40,613 --> 00:11:41,880
and a few things I'm moving over.

188
00:11:42,526 --> 00:11:43,926
What things?

189
00:11:44,206 --> 00:11:45,706
Just some things.

190
00:11:46,626 --> 00:11:49,465
Anyway, I'm working on the follow-up
program to the people-finder app,

191
00:11:49,466 --> 00:11:50,466
and it's almost finished.

192
00:11:51,206 --> 00:11:52,839
You've already started another project?

193
00:11:52,839 --> 00:11:55,406
Yes, I worked on it
whenever I had free time during Lucky Joy.

194
00:11:55,846 --> 00:11:58,406
It's a new program that's mine alone.
It's not owned by Kangsu Construction.

195
00:11:59,312 --> 00:12:01,505
So that's why you accepted
my internship offer?

196
00:12:01,506 --> 00:12:03,005
To take it back?

197
00:12:03,006 --> 00:12:04,572
Take it back?

198
00:12:04,573 --> 00:12:08,059
I was just reclaiming what belonged to me
and wasn't covered by the contract.

199
00:12:09,240 --> 00:12:10,806
So what kind of program is it?

200
00:12:11,779 --> 00:12:14,279
It's called Mind Post Office,
and it's a mental wellness app.

201
00:12:14,819 --> 00:12:17,512
The idea is to send feelings
you've never been able to send to someone.

202
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:19,120
Take a look.

203
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:24,333
You know how everyone
has things like that.

204
00:12:25,213 --> 00:12:26,818
Things they want to tell someone,

205
00:12:26,818 --> 00:12:28,512
but can never bring themselves to say,

206
00:12:29,553 --> 00:12:31,606
things they want to hide,
things they'd rather forget,

207
00:12:32,246 --> 00:12:34,546
but can't keep bottled up forever.

208
00:12:35,512 --> 00:12:38,632
This isn't medical treatment or therapy.

209
00:12:39,393 --> 00:12:41,279
It's simply a place
to talk through your feelings.

210
00:12:41,579 --> 00:12:42,739
A place to unburden your heart.

211
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:46,432
Do you think I'm hiding...

212
00:12:46,886 --> 00:12:48,046
some deep emotional wound?

213
00:12:48,959 --> 00:12:52,293
I'm not sure, but maybe at first,
I created this...

214
00:12:52,906 --> 00:12:56,273
for the version of myself
who believed my mom had abandoned me.

215
00:12:57,453 --> 00:13:01,086
Back then, it was a deep wound
I couldn't share with anyone.

216
00:13:02,146 --> 00:13:03,686
Of course, I've worked through it now.

217
00:13:04,746 --> 00:13:06,786
You're the first person I'm showing it to,

218
00:13:07,053 --> 00:13:08,686
so try it out
and tell me what needs improving.

219
00:13:11,046 --> 00:13:13,066
You think I'm actually going to use this?

220
00:13:13,173 --> 00:13:14,999
Well, if you don't want to, that's fine.

221
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:17,160
Just so you know,

222
00:13:17,460 --> 00:13:21,073
if a user sets their counseling records
to completely private,

223
00:13:21,339 --> 00:13:23,799
not even the developer can access them.

224
00:13:24,420 --> 00:13:26,193
Everything is fully encrypted,

225
00:13:26,839 --> 00:13:29,173
so you don't have to worry
about your privacy.

226
00:13:33,792 --> 00:13:36,193
(Kangsu Construction)

227
00:13:38,826 --> 00:13:42,126
Everyone worked hard yesterday.
We couldn't even have our team dinner.

228
00:13:42,339 --> 00:13:44,699
How about tonight? I know a great spot.

229
00:13:44,859 --> 00:13:48,113
Not today. Let's pick another day
that works better.

230
00:13:48,739 --> 00:13:50,866
By the way, is something going on
with Mr. Han Ji Hun?

231
00:13:51,086 --> 00:13:53,233
I haven't been able to reach him
since he left the presentation yesterday.

232
00:13:53,633 --> 00:13:56,533
He told me something came up at home
and took a leave of absence.

233
00:13:59,553 --> 00:14:00,786
What? A leave of absence?

234
00:14:01,232 --> 00:14:03,132
All right, everyone.
Let's give it our all...

235
00:14:03,640 --> 00:14:05,140
for the final third round.

236
00:14:05,373 --> 00:14:06,406
Let's finish strong.

237
00:14:07,640 --> 00:14:09,340
Manager Seo,
come to my office for a moment.

238
00:14:13,653 --> 00:14:16,739
Team Manager, Ms. Cho, congratulations.

239
00:14:17,166 --> 00:14:18,373
Sorry? For what?

240
00:14:18,606 --> 00:14:20,213
You totally surprised us yesterday.

241
00:14:20,366 --> 00:14:21,806
I had my suspicions, of course.

242
00:14:22,066 --> 00:14:25,433
Me too.
I had a feeling, but I wasn't sure.

243
00:14:26,179 --> 00:14:29,006
Thanks. Now I can stop hiding it.

244
00:14:30,126 --> 00:14:31,126
Seriously, Team Manager...

245
00:14:33,486 --> 00:14:35,652
About Mr. Han Ji Hun...

246
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:37,933
I'd like to handle it quietly myself.

247
00:14:38,959 --> 00:14:40,059
What do you think, Manager Seo?

248
00:14:40,906 --> 00:14:43,873
I'm sure you have your reasons
for wanting to keep it quiet.

249
00:14:44,320 --> 00:14:45,320
Understood.

250
00:14:45,733 --> 00:14:46,733
Thanks.

251
00:14:47,553 --> 00:14:49,439
And, about us...

252
00:14:50,306 --> 00:14:51,406
Could we talk?

253
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:55,506
I'd appreciate it if you could
spare some time after work today.

254
00:14:56,946 --> 00:14:57,946
Just a moment.

255
00:15:00,373 --> 00:15:01,373
Hello?

256
00:15:01,793 --> 00:15:04,213
What? Okay.

257
00:15:05,166 --> 00:15:06,919
Chief, I'd like to take the day off today.

258
00:15:07,160 --> 00:15:09,700
A day off? What happened all of a sudden?

259
00:15:10,013 --> 00:15:11,013
I'm sorry.

260
00:15:18,059 --> 00:15:19,812
Did you really have to go that far?

261
00:15:20,926 --> 00:15:23,233
What are you talking about? Speak clearly.

262
00:15:23,620 --> 00:15:26,159
If Team Manager Ko really is ill,

263
00:15:26,786 --> 00:15:28,453
then as his father, your first concern
should be for his well-being.

264
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:32,479
How could you use that against him
to take him down?

265
00:15:33,273 --> 00:15:36,373
What? Do you have any proof?

266
00:15:37,846 --> 00:15:40,446
You must be saying this because of
what the Chairman said yesterday.

267
00:15:41,340 --> 00:15:43,779
It wasn't me. He got it wrong.

268
00:15:43,953 --> 00:15:46,600
I sincerely hope it wasn't you.

269
00:15:47,786 --> 00:15:49,819
At least if you understand even a fraction
of the Chairman's intentions.

270
00:15:51,740 --> 00:15:54,240
You're crossing a line, Mr. Cho.

271
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:56,060
What's this supposed to mean?

272
00:15:56,620 --> 00:15:58,439
Are you openly trying...

273
00:15:58,439 --> 00:16:00,286
to act like the Chairman's son-in-law
in front of me?

274
00:16:01,379 --> 00:16:02,719
For the final round of the competition,

275
00:16:03,546 --> 00:16:06,219
don't do anything
that compromises its fairness.

276
00:16:07,646 --> 00:16:08,846
I'll be watching.

277
00:16:09,326 --> 00:16:11,306
Watching?

278
00:16:11,779 --> 00:16:12,779
An assistant watching the CEO?

279
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,000
What? Are you warning me now?

280
00:16:16,153 --> 00:16:17,753
It's not a warning. It's advice.

281
00:16:19,226 --> 00:16:20,226
Take it to heart.

282
00:16:24,866 --> 00:16:27,146
Advice?

283
00:16:28,139 --> 00:16:30,933
That punk...
I can't even fire him. Unbelievable.

284
00:16:31,473 --> 00:16:34,159
Hold on.
Why do I feel something coming on?

285
00:16:34,866 --> 00:16:36,993
Is it my blood pressure? Seriously...

286
00:16:37,399 --> 00:16:38,399
Really?

287
00:16:43,566 --> 00:16:44,566
Packing another lunch?

288
00:16:44,912 --> 00:16:47,632
Yeah. The food outside...

289
00:16:47,633 --> 00:16:49,012
just isn't to my taste.

290
00:16:49,426 --> 00:16:51,759
Your home cooking is still the best, Mom.

291
00:16:52,933 --> 00:16:55,466
I don't think there's a single one
of my side dishes in today's lunch.

292
00:16:56,892 --> 00:16:58,713
Mom, come on. You should try some too.

293
00:16:58,840 --> 00:17:00,366
Grandma's food is really delicious.

294
00:17:00,673 --> 00:17:02,959
Enough chatter. Get to the studio.

295
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:05,459
Yes, I'm off.

296
00:17:10,833 --> 00:17:14,613
Looks like your wish came true.
Your son-in-law and grandchildren ate it.

297
00:17:18,153 --> 00:17:19,846
Lunch was absolutely delicious.

298
00:17:20,146 --> 00:17:23,033
Especially the braised short ribs.
Best I've ever had.

299
00:17:23,919 --> 00:17:24,919
They were that good.

300
00:17:25,213 --> 00:17:27,439
I'm glad you liked them.

301
00:17:29,812 --> 00:17:33,226
Since we're both bringing lunch every day,

302
00:17:33,226 --> 00:17:34,599
it seems like we have too much food.

303
00:17:35,253 --> 00:17:37,919
How about we take turns from now on?

304
00:17:38,786 --> 00:17:39,959
You bring it on odd days,
and I'll bring it on even days.

305
00:17:41,306 --> 00:17:43,659
Odd days, you. Even days, me.

306
00:17:43,659 --> 00:17:44,913
O-Y-E-M?

307
00:17:45,626 --> 00:17:47,939
Well, okay.

308
00:17:50,946 --> 00:17:53,153
What's wrong?
Is your stomach bothering you?

309
00:17:54,426 --> 00:17:55,959
Don't tell me it's number two?

310
00:17:59,286 --> 00:18:01,913
Rule number four.
Number two in the outside restroom.

311
00:18:02,626 --> 00:18:04,272
You made that rule.

312
00:18:04,273 --> 00:18:06,766
It's not that.

313
00:18:07,299 --> 00:18:08,813
What should we do?

314
00:18:11,753 --> 00:18:14,679
Come to think of it, I think...

315
00:18:14,680 --> 00:18:16,859
they've been doing construction
on that outside restroom for days.

316
00:18:17,593 --> 00:18:19,713
I said that's not it.
Why do you keep saying that?

317
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:23,660
Excuse me.

318
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,593
Could you hurry out
and get me an iced Americano?

319
00:18:27,499 --> 00:18:29,553
Extra ice. Hurry!

320
00:18:47,626 --> 00:18:50,839
Bung Nim,
don't steal Bung Wu's food, okay?

321
00:18:50,839 --> 00:18:52,299
Keep it up, and you'll be...

322
00:18:57,646 --> 00:18:59,639
I'm heading toward Onse Intersection now.

323
00:19:01,246 --> 00:19:02,832
Do not hang up.

324
00:19:03,246 --> 00:19:05,513
You know what'll happen to your daughter
the moment you do.

325
00:19:08,573 --> 00:19:10,639
I'm in front
of the CS convenience store ATM.

326
00:19:10,919 --> 00:19:12,206
Please hurry!

327
00:19:23,366 --> 00:19:24,366
Damn it.

328
00:19:24,793 --> 00:19:25,793
Stop right there!

329
00:19:31,186 --> 00:19:32,253
You called the police, didn't you?

330
00:19:33,199 --> 00:19:35,039
You're really asking for it.

331
00:19:35,606 --> 00:19:36,606
Don't come any closer.

332
00:19:36,846 --> 00:19:37,966
One more step,

333
00:19:38,226 --> 00:19:40,786
and this girl's dead!

334
00:19:41,226 --> 00:19:42,226
Let her go. Now!

335
00:19:42,372 --> 00:19:44,479
Taking a hostage
will only add to your sentence.

336
00:19:45,146 --> 00:19:46,679
I've got nothing left to lose anyway.

337
00:19:47,039 --> 00:19:48,846
Five years or six, what's the difference?

338
00:19:52,946 --> 00:19:53,946
Stay still.

339
00:19:58,066 --> 00:19:59,066
Let go!

340
00:19:59,399 --> 00:20:00,399
- Let go!
- Seung Ri, are you okay?

341
00:20:00,399 --> 00:20:01,399
You're under arrest
for aggravated intimidation...

342
00:20:01,399 --> 00:20:03,865
- and voice phishing.
- Min Ho.

343
00:20:04,033 --> 00:20:05,219
What happened?

344
00:20:05,753 --> 00:20:08,552
- Are you hurt? Let me see.
- Let go!

345
00:20:08,552 --> 00:20:11,031
- Are you hurt anywhere else?
- You have the right to remain silent...

346
00:20:11,032 --> 00:20:12,032
- I'm fine.
- and to refuse to make any statement.

347
00:20:12,032 --> 00:20:13,199
You also have the right to an attorney.

348
00:20:13,199 --> 00:20:15,126
Let go!

349
00:20:16,072 --> 00:20:17,820
Let go!

350
00:20:21,106 --> 00:20:22,293
What are you doing here?

351
00:20:22,646 --> 00:20:24,132
How did you...

352
00:20:24,132 --> 00:20:25,373
Is that really what's important right now?

353
00:20:26,126 --> 00:20:27,126
Can you stand?

354
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,400
Let's get you to the hospital first.

355
00:20:32,539 --> 00:20:33,539
Are you all right?

356
00:20:33,900 --> 00:20:35,366
You're the one who reported
the voice phishing scam, right?

357
00:20:35,933 --> 00:20:37,166
Yes. That's me.

358
00:20:37,913 --> 00:20:38,972
A voice phishing scam?

359
00:20:39,766 --> 00:20:42,638
If you're okay, we'd like you to come
with us and give a witness statement.

360
00:20:42,639 --> 00:20:44,713
No. I have nothing to say.

361
00:20:45,259 --> 00:20:47,426
I just happened to overhear
the phone call while passing by.

362
00:20:48,166 --> 00:20:49,953
She has nothing to say. You should go.

363
00:20:50,346 --> 00:20:51,833
She should see a doctor first.

364
00:20:52,733 --> 00:20:54,052
All right. Please get treated,

365
00:20:54,179 --> 00:20:56,272
and let us know
if you discover any additional losses.

366
00:21:01,066 --> 00:21:02,066
Min Ho.

367
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:06,006
Please don't tell my parents about today.

368
00:21:06,746 --> 00:21:08,073
They'll only worry.

369
00:21:08,366 --> 00:21:09,946
Is that really what you're worried about
right now?

370
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:13,073
Fine.
But let's get you to the hospital first.

371
00:21:16,239 --> 00:21:17,833
What? Who was arrested?

372
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:20,860
No, I wasn't harmed.

373
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:23,053
He was part of a voice phishing ring.

374
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:25,492
Jeong Dong Pal's call log
included your number,

375
00:21:25,493 --> 00:21:28,453
so we called to check for any losses.
Glad to hear you're okay.

376
00:21:36,319 --> 00:21:38,486
What's wrong? What happened now?

377
00:21:39,119 --> 00:21:40,526
Nothing.

378
00:21:42,539 --> 00:21:45,106
Who was that?
Why do you keep getting these calls?

379
00:21:46,326 --> 00:21:48,893
Don't worry. It's all been taken care of.

380
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:52,732
Taken care of? What happened?

381
00:21:54,373 --> 00:21:56,726
I'll tell you later.

382
00:22:04,592 --> 00:22:06,966
Seung Ri, what happened to your arm?

383
00:22:07,739 --> 00:22:10,493
You're hurt? Where? How?

384
00:22:11,653 --> 00:22:13,253
It's nothing, so don't worry.

385
00:22:17,181 --> 00:22:20,426
I was riding a bike to exercise,
and I fell off.

386
00:22:20,426 --> 00:22:21,426
Don't worry.

387
00:22:21,766 --> 00:22:23,979
You were riding a bike? With who?

388
00:22:24,953 --> 00:22:26,779
Min Ho, by any chance?

389
00:22:27,300 --> 00:22:30,106
What? Yes.

390
00:22:31,346 --> 00:22:32,879
You should've been more careful.

391
00:22:33,619 --> 00:22:35,079
You can't go getting scars.

392
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:36,600
Did you go to the hospital?

393
00:22:37,266 --> 00:22:38,266
Of course.

394
00:22:38,686 --> 00:22:40,312
Min Ho must've been so worried.

395
00:22:40,886 --> 00:22:44,059
Seung Ri's hurt,
and all you can think about is Chief Ko?

396
00:22:44,679 --> 00:22:46,046
Why do you think?

397
00:22:46,446 --> 00:22:49,031
It's because our son-in-law
treasures Seung Ri...

398
00:22:49,032 --> 00:22:50,566
more than he treasures himself.

399
00:22:51,340 --> 00:22:53,639
Any other bruises anywhere?

400
00:22:54,199 --> 00:22:55,326
No.

401
00:22:56,586 --> 00:22:58,519
I'll go to my room now.

402
00:22:58,813 --> 00:23:00,179
Okay. Get some rest.

403
00:23:11,773 --> 00:23:13,139
Why are you making seaweed soup, Mother?

404
00:23:14,673 --> 00:23:15,806
Did you add perilla seed powder?

405
00:23:17,299 --> 00:23:19,553
Seaweed soup with perilla seed powder
isn't really my thing.

406
00:23:19,946 --> 00:23:22,372
You should've made it
with beef or abalone.

407
00:23:23,793 --> 00:23:26,286
Perilla seeds are really good for you,
right?

408
00:23:26,666 --> 00:23:29,206
They're rich in omega-three fatty acids
and antioxidants.

409
00:23:29,479 --> 00:23:31,126
They're great for your skin. Really great.

410
00:23:33,319 --> 00:23:34,499
You two enjoy your conversation.

411
00:23:34,706 --> 00:23:36,373
I'll head in now.

412
00:23:41,506 --> 00:23:43,006
So today's the day.

413
00:23:44,386 --> 00:23:45,486
Want me to come with you?

414
00:23:48,086 --> 00:23:49,999
She won't eat it even if I take it.

415
00:23:52,006 --> 00:23:53,706
Maybe I shouldn't have done this.

416
00:23:55,053 --> 00:23:57,552
If she can't even eat...

417
00:23:57,553 --> 00:23:59,459
because of me today...

418
00:24:00,113 --> 00:24:03,426
That's exactly why
you have to keep trying. Don't feel small.

419
00:24:08,299 --> 00:24:09,299
What does he mean?

420
00:24:10,326 --> 00:24:12,852
Seaweed soup and today's the day?

421
00:24:17,286 --> 00:24:19,559
Honey, today's the day!

422
00:24:19,753 --> 00:24:21,200
Today's that girl's...

423
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:23,493
I mean, Kang Yeon Ja's birthday.

424
00:24:24,526 --> 00:24:26,506
What? Today's her real birthday?

425
00:24:27,019 --> 00:24:28,086
That's right.

426
00:24:28,453 --> 00:24:32,226
Mother made seaweed soup
to take over there.

427
00:24:33,286 --> 00:24:34,286
Really?

428
00:24:36,186 --> 00:24:37,186
Then...

429
00:24:37,720 --> 00:24:39,859
- It's 0704.
- It's 0704?

430
00:24:50,773 --> 00:24:52,266
I've had enough of this.

431
00:24:53,513 --> 00:24:55,759
Should I just disappear again?

432
00:24:56,746 --> 00:24:59,266
How much longer is this going to go on?

433
00:24:59,519 --> 00:25:00,839
I'll go inside for a moment.

434
00:25:03,299 --> 00:25:05,853
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

435
00:25:19,386 --> 00:25:22,419
What are you doing in my kitchen?

436
00:25:23,273 --> 00:25:24,806
You may not remember,

437
00:25:26,093 --> 00:25:28,093
but today is your real birthday.

438
00:25:29,079 --> 00:25:30,079
What?

439
00:25:31,866 --> 00:25:35,233
Today is my real birthday?

440
00:25:36,386 --> 00:25:37,919
You were passed
from one orphanage to another.

441
00:25:39,653 --> 00:25:41,886
Even your birthday
and your name were wrong.

442
00:25:43,159 --> 00:25:44,372
After we were separated,

443
00:25:46,000 --> 00:25:48,699
you never got to celebrate
your real birthday again, did you?

444
00:25:50,733 --> 00:25:51,733
So you know.

445
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,920
I lived my whole life
without even knowing my real birthday.

446
00:25:54,920 --> 00:25:56,153
And I never needed to know.

447
00:25:57,013 --> 00:25:58,686
My own mother abandoned me.

448
00:25:59,073 --> 00:26:01,059
Why would the day I was born matter?

449
00:26:01,600 --> 00:26:04,973
I understand why you'd feel that way.

450
00:26:07,059 --> 00:26:08,712
I know I don't deserve it,

451
00:26:09,973 --> 00:26:10,973
but today...

452
00:26:11,979 --> 00:26:15,126
I really wanted you
to have the seaweed soup I made.

453
00:26:16,473 --> 00:26:19,799
I'll go now,
so please have at least one spoonful.

454
00:26:27,906 --> 00:26:31,866
Happy birthday, my dear.

455
00:27:53,080 --> 00:27:54,080
Mom.

456
00:28:00,346 --> 00:28:01,346
Mom.

457
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:06,040
Mom.

458
00:28:22,813 --> 00:28:24,513
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
